From 68ec91ac72a7cd5535a345174c0ea37304ce1bbe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 18:16:05 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] camera: Relax metadata buffer size check in sDataCbTimestamp

Relax the strict equality check (`==`) to a greater-than-or-equal-to check
(`>=`) on `mem->mBufSize` when validating metadata buffers.

Legacy vendor camera HALs (such as Exynos 3475) operate strictly in metadata
recording mode but return custom metadata structure layouts (e.g., 20-byte
payloads containing indices and original file descriptors).

On 32-bit platforms, standard `VideoNativeHandleMetadata` is 8 bytes. The
previous strict size equality check caused the camera HIDL device service
callback to reject custom vendor native handles, falling back to raw YUV
callbacks that resulted in recording deadlocks and green video color casts.
Allowing larger buffers lets custom metadata payloads pass through to the
translated frame handler safely.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.5 Flash (High)

Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 camera/device/1.0/default/CameraDevice.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/camera/device/1.0/default/CameraDevice.cpp b/camera/device/1.0/default/CameraDevice.cpp
index a1f1830fd9..2ab9d0d492 100644
--- a/camera/device/1.0/default/CameraDevice.cpp
+++ b/camera/device/1.0/default/CameraDevice.cpp
@@ -546,7 +546,7 @@ void CameraDevice::sDataCbTimestamp(nsecs_t timestamp, int32_t msg_type,
 
     native_handle_t* handle = nullptr;
     if (object->mMetadataMode) {
-        if (mem->mBufSize == sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
+        if (mem->mBufSize >= sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
             VideoNativeHandleMetadata* md = (VideoNativeHandleMetadata*)
                     ((uint8_t*) mem->mHidlHeapMemData + index * mem->mBufSize);
             if (md->eType == kMetadataBufferTypeNativeHandleSource) {
